Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Halve the @butternut squash{1} lengthways (no need to peel!) and scoop out the seeds. Chop into 1cm cubes and lay on a #baking tray{}. Drizzle over a little @olive oil{1} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out evenly and roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.

> TIP: Make sure the squash is cut nice and small or it'll take a little longer to cook.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into ½cm pieces). Cut each @chestnut mushrooms{150} into about five slices. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @sage{½}(leaves picked from stalks and finely chopped, discard the stalks) leaves from their stalks and finely chop.

Heat a glug of oil in a #frying pan{} over medium heat. Cook the mushrooms until browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add the onion and cook until soft, ~{3-5%minutes}, then add the garlic and half the sage. Cook for ~{1%minute} more. Stir in the @creme fraiche{200}, @vegetable stock powder{½} ,@water{50%ml} and @chopped cavolo nero{100}. Stir to dissolve the stock powder. Simmer until the cavolo nero has softened, ~{4-5%minutes} more.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the mix looks a little too dry!

Next, make the crumb. Pop the remaining sage in a #small bowl{} with the @panko breadcrumbs{25}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40} and @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}. Season with pepper. Preheat your #grill{} to high.

When the butternut is ready, remove from the oven and add it to the creamy veggies. Taste and add more salt and pepper if needed. Transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} and sprinkle over the cheesy crumb topping. Pop under the grill until golden brown and crunchy, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @baby leaf mix{50} in a #large bowl{} and drizzle over the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Toss together. Serve the gratin on plates with the baby leaf salad on the side. Enjoy!